        <p class="metadata">Posted by Matthew Weier O'Phinney (matthew) on 2009-08-21T12:53:12.000+0000</p> 
        <div class="body">
            <p>ZF-6803 resolves this issue.</p>

<p>If you define your default module bootstrap using Zend_Application_Module_Bootstrap, and place it in a directory named 'default', then yes, you should prefix your various module resources with the verbiage 'Default_'. In most cases, and all examples in the ZF manual, the default module is also the home of the application bootstrap, and as such, this is something you need to define for yourself (i.e., whether you want your default module resources prefixed, and if so, with what prefix).</p>

